There is a little more freedom after two years of lockdown restrictions. President Cyril Ramaphosa has announced several changes to health regulations. #DStv403 #eNCA PRETORIA - Masks are no longer required when outdoors but they will still be required at indoor facilities.
President Cyril Ramaphosa announced regulation changes during an address to the nation on Tuesday night. READ | SA Lockdown | Calls to scrap COVID-19 regulations Ramaphosa also announced that the state of disaster will end after the public has commented on proposed new regulations.
The president is also urging the unvaccinated to get the COVID-19 jab. There's been a steady decline in the number of coronavirus cases countrywide over the past few weeks.